selector.name: data()
selector.description: Attaches data to, or gets data from, selected elements

selector.name: each()
selector.description: Execute a function for each matched element

selector.name: get()
selector.description: Get the DOM elements matched by the selector

selector.name: index()
selector.description: Search for a given element from among the matched elements

selector.name: $.noConflict()
selector.description: Release jQuery's control of the $ variable

selector.name: $.param()
selector.description: Create a serialized representation of an array or object (can be used as URL query string for AJAX requests)

selector.name: removeData()
selector.description: Removes a previously-stored piece of data

selector.name: size()
selector.description: Removed in version 3.0. Use the length property instead

selector.name: toArray()
selector.description: Retrieve all the DOM elements contained in the jQuery set, as an array
